                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="illustration">Illustrated throughout: f.4a the cat making its way to the tavern;
                        f.4b the mice cavort; f.5b the cat seizes a mouse; f. 6b the cat takes up
                        residence in the mosque; f.7b a delegation of mice bearing gifts; f.8a the
                        cat attacks the mice; f.9b the army of mice gathers; f.10b the army of cats
                        gathers; f.11a the cat captive before the mice; f.11b the vizier of the mice
                        accompanies the cat; f.12a the vizier of the mice is slaughtered by the
                        cats; f13a the army of the mice captures the cat; f.14a the mice execute the
                        cat. </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <accMat>
                     <note> f. 1b. Note: ‘Moosh-Nama, a very rare mock heroic Poem by Obed Zakany –
                        J.B. Elliott. Patna April 10th 1846’ </note>
                  </accMat>
